mention.text: the mirth , which else had swelled as shrill As a school let loose to its errant will
That in a dim hushed room above A mother 's pains in a mother 's love
The story of that precious life

That wandering hand which seemed to reach At angel finger-tips , And that murmur like a mystic speech Upon the rosy lips , That something in the serious face Holier than even its infant grace , And that rapt gaze on empty space , Which made us , half believing , say , " Ah , little wide-eyed seer !
the gloom of the chamber where he died , And by that grave which , through our care , From Yule to Yule of every year , Is made like spring to bloom ; And where , at times

the sigh As of an angel floating nigh , Who longs but has not power to tell That in that violet-shrouded cell Lies nothing better than the shell Which he had cast aside -- By that sweet grave , in that dark room , We may weave at will for each other 's ear , Of that life , and that love , and that early doom
The tale which is shadowed here : To us alone it will always be As fresh as our own misery ; But enough
